The paper focuses on video description using attention mechanisms and neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) fields. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with multimodal fusion, which involves combining information from multiple modalities, making cs.MM a likely sub-category. The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms also suggests cs.LG as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for video description, indicating that it may fall under the cs.AI sub-category.
